{"name": "python-simple-logger", "metadata": {"name": "python-simple-logger", "version": "2.0.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/RedHatQE/python-simple-logger", "license": "Apache-2.0", "documentation_url": "https://github.com/RedHatQE/python-simple-logger/blob/main/README.md", "dependencies": ["colorlog"], "summary": "A simple logger for python", "upload_time": 1732715978}, "documentation": ["# Simple Python logger\n\nA simple logger for console/file logging with duplicate logs filter support\n\n## Release new version\n\n### requirements\n\n- Export GitHub token\n\n```bash\nexport GITHUB_TOKEN=<your_github_token>\n```\n\n- [release-it](https://github.com/release-it/release-it)\n\nRun the following once (execute outside repository dir for example `~/`):\n\n```bash\nsudo npm install --global release-it\nnpm install --save-dev @release-it/bumper\n```\n\n### usage\n\n- Create a release\n\n```bash\ngit pull\nrelease-it # Follow the instructions\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\nfrom simple_logger.logger import get_logger\nlogger = get_logger(name=__name__, level=logging.DEBUG, filename=\"my-log.log\")\nlogger.info(\"This is INFO log\")\nlogger.success(\"This is SUCCESS log\")\n\nTOKEN = \"1234\"\nPASS = \"pass123\"\nlogger.hash(f\"This is my password: {PASS} and this is my token {TOKEN}\", hash=[PASS, TOKEN])\n>>> This is INFO log\n>>> This is SUCCESS log\n>>> This is my password: ***** and this is my token *****\n\n\n# mask sensitive data default words are [\"password\", \"token\", \"apikey\", \"secret\"]\n# Pass mask_sensitive_patterns = [\"custom_pattern\", \"another_pattern\"] to change the default patterns to match\nhashed_logger = get_logger(name=__name__, mask_sensitive=True)\nhashed_logger.info(er = get\"This is my password: pass123\")\nhashed_logger.info(er = get\"This is my token tok456!\")\nhashed_logger.info(er = get\"This is my apikey - api#$789\")\nhashed_logger.info(er = get\"This is my secret -> sec1234abc\")\n>>> This is my password *****\n>>> This is my token *****\n>>> This is my apikey *****\n>>> This is my secret *****\n```\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "simple_logger.tests", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "simple_logger.tests.test_logger", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "simple_logger.tests.test_logger.tmp_log_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "tmp_path_factory", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_logger.tests.test_logger.basic_logger", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "tmp_log_file", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_logger.tests.test_logger.logger_with_mask", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "tmp_log_file", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_logger.tests.test_logger.logger_with_mask_and_pattarns", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "tmp_log_file", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_logger.tests.test_logger.test_mask_sensitive", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "tmp_log_file", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "logger_with_mask", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "logger_with_mask_and_pattarns", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_logger.tests.test_logger.test_existing_logger", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_logger.tests.test_logger.test_disable_console_logging", "asynchronous": false, "params